  {
    "label": "Combo: Article Example",
    "description": "Here's the full write-up on how AUI works:",
    "aui": {
      "display": "sheet",
      "sheet_title": "About AUI",
      "steps": [
        {
          "label": "Article",
          "skippable": false,
          "blocks": [
            { "type": "heading", "data": { "text": "What is Adaptive UI?" } },
            { "type": "caption", "data": { "text": "5 min read · Updated April 2026" } },
            { "type": "text", "data": { "text": "Adaptive UI (AUI) is a catalog-driven format that lets AI assistants respond with native interactive components inside a chat conversation — not just plain text. Instead of designing UI, the AI picks from a pre-built catalog of components, fills in the data, and the library renders them natively." } },

            { "type": "divider" },

            { "type": "heading", "data": { "text": "Why a catalog, not a layout language?" } },
            { "type": "text", "data": { "text": "Letting an AI design arbitrary UI from scratch creates two problems: inconsistent visual quality, and unbounded token cost. A catalog flips both. The AI picks from a finite set of components that the host app has already designed, themed, and tested. The AI's job shrinks from *designing* to *choosing*." } },
            { "type": "text", "data": { "text": "The trade-off is expressiveness — you can only show what the catalog supports. In practice, this is the right constraint for chat. A well-designed catalog of 30-50 components covers the vast majority of useful chat interactions: polls, forms, product cards, confirmations, rich status updates." } },

            { "type": "divider" },

            { "type": "heading", "data": { "text": "Three display levels" } },
            { "type": "text", "data": { "text": "**Inline** — renders inside the AI's chat bubble. Quick confirmations, simple status, a button or two." } },
            { "type": "text", "data": { "text": "**Expanded** — renders full-width in the chat feed, below the bubble. Product cards, galleries, rich lists." } },
            { "type": "text", "data": { "text": "**Sheet** — renders as a bottom sheet overlay. Multi-step surveys, forms, focused input flows. Also works for long-form content like this article." } },
            { "type": "caption", "data": { "text": "The AI picks the display level per response based on what's appropriate." } },

            { "type": "divider" },

            { "type": "heading", "data": { "text": "Closing the loop" } },
            { "type": "text", "data": { "text": "When a user interacts with a rendered component — taps a button, selects a chip, submits a form — the result becomes the next user message in the conversation. This is what makes AUI *conversational*: every interaction feeds back into the dialogue, and the AI responds to the interaction just like it would to typed text." } },

            { "type": "divider" },

            { "type": "caption", "data": { "text": "AUI is open-source and available at github.com/bennyjon/aui" } },

            {
              "type": "button_primary",
              "data": { "label": "Got it" },
              "feedback": { "action": "submit", "params": { "article": "about_aui", "read": true } }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  }
